        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Our Scottsdale resort has multiple restaurants and banquet kitchens. How does fire code apply to each?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Each commercial cooking operation with a hood-and-duct system on your resort requires its own semi-annual NFPA 96 inspection. A resort with three restaurants, one banquet kitchen, and room service prep areas may have five or more separate systems — each requiring independent inspection and documentation. Coordinate all inspections simultaneously to avoid staggered compliance gaps.</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does every Scottsdale restaurant need a kitchen fire suppression system?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. All commercial cooking operations in Scottsdale producing grease-laden vapors must have an automatic wet chemical suppression system under NFPA 96 and the Arizona Fire Code (IFC-based). This applies to restaurants, bars with food service, hotel kitchens, and corporate cafeterias.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often does kitchen fire suppression need to be inspected in Scottsdale?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">NFPA 96 requires semi-annual inspection — twice per year — for all commercial kitchen suppression systems. Inspection must be performed by a licensed contractor and documented. The Scottsdale Fire Department enforces this requirement.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does kitchen suppression inspection cost in Scottsdale?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">$175–$400 per system per system. Budget for two inspections annually.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What is the most common kitchen fire safety violation in Scottsdale?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Common violations in Scottsdale include: Overdue semi-annual suppression inspection in Old Town bar and restaurant kitchens; Multiple suppression systems at resort properties with staggered inspection dates.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who licenses kitchen suppression contractors in AZ?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Arizona State Fire Marshal's Office ((602) 364-1003) licenses fire protection contractors statewide. Verify your suppression contractor holds current AZ credentials before scheduling service.</p></div></div>
